Exam:   US LT BREAST TARGETED

Technique:  Targeted imaging of the  right breast  is performed.

Findings:\r\n\r\nTargeted imaging of the left breast is performed from the 6:00 to the 9:00 position.  

At the 6:00 position, 5 cm from the nipple, there is a 3 x 2 x 4 mm minimally hypoechoic mass with a peripheral calcification. This may correspond to the mammographic finding. No other cystic or solid masses visualized.

result.description: CLINICALLY SIGNIFICANT MASS, TUMOR, OR INFECTION
